      • getAttributes

        public String[] getAttributes()
        Get the Text formatting/usage attributes.

        Supported attributes: 

           BOLD               print in bold (if supported by POS printer)
   DOUBLE_HEIGHT      print double height (if supported by POS printer)
   DOUBLE_WIDTH       print double width (if supported by POS printer)
   CENTRE             space-pad text within printwidth to print centre-line
   RIGHT              space-pad text to print right-justified within print width
   SPLIT              space-pad text to left & right justify each side of '^'
   Default is single height left justified.

   BARCODE            print text (must be a number string) as a barcode (if supported by POS printer)

   JOURNAL            text is for journal storage, not direct printing
        Returns:
        attributes

      • setAttributes

        public void setAttributes​(String[] attributes)
        Set the Text formatting/usage attributes.

        Supported attributes: 

           BOLD               print in bold (if supported by POS printer)
   DOUBLE_HEIGHT      print double height (if supported by POS printer)
   DOUBLE_WIDTH       print double width (if supported by POS printer)
   CENTRE             space-pad text within printwidth to print centre-line
   RIGHT              space-pad text to print right-justified within print width
   SPLIT              space-pad text to left & right justify each side of '^'
   Default is single height left justified.

   BARCODE            print text (must be a number string) as a barcode (if supported by POS printer)

   JOURNAL            text is for journal storage, not direct printing
        Parameters:
        attributes - the attributes
